Waze / Economic Shock Test

Dan Flynn | Volpe

Overview

  • Test data for economic recovery from natural disasters example
  • Find counties impacted by Hurricane Florence, do county level total reports of different types by day,
  • Compare to previous year

Queried Waze data for North Carolina, and prepared data as counts of Waze report types by day. Overlayed with county FIPS, and filtered to manually selected counties with varying levels of impact, using FEMA disaster declaration. Disaster was declared on September 14, 2018, and the official incident period was September 7 to 29, 2018. No disasters were declared in North Carolina in 2017.

Selected counties:

Using data from May to November of each 2017 and 2018, in total there were 6,043,010 Waze reports in NC.

The vertical line in the plots below mark the disaster declaration on September 14, 2018.
